skos:Collection.skos:prefLabel: BODC parameter semantic model parameter entity names
skos:Collection.dc:title: BODC parameter semantic model parameter entity names
skos:Collection.dc:description: Controlled vocabulary defining the terms that may be used for a parameter entity (part of the what theme) in the BODC parameter semantic model.
skos:Collection.dc:creator: British Oceanographic Data Centre
skos:Collection.rdfs:comment: Governance for vocabularies used within the data centre

skos:Concept.skos:definition: The age of an object determined by radiocarbon dating expressed relative to a datum of AD 1950.
A measure of the quantity of incident electromagnetic radiation that is absorbed by an object, substance or solution.
The number of occurrences of an entity per unit area or per unit volume.
The rate at which the quantity of an entity increases.
The number of disintegrations of a radioactive substance in a given unit of time (physics) or in the ability of a substance to take part in a chemical reaction (chemistry).
The difference between the measured chemical susbtance concentration and its equilibrium saturation concentration in a matrix with the same physical and chemical properties.
The amount of organism per unit area or per unit volume expressed as mass or amount of a chemical constituent.
The surface area of organisms per unit area of per unit volume.
The volume of of organisms per unit area of per unit volume.
The volume of a single cell or the average volume of single cells.
The rate at which the quantity of an entity decreases.
The amount of a specified substance in a unit amount of another substance or matrix.
Concentration expressed in terms of carbon.
The difference between the concentration of a substance at a given time minus its concentration at an earlier time divided by the time elapsed between the two time points.
The concentration of a substance in solution calculated as the equivalent in a zero salinity solution.
The number of occurrences of an entity.
The speed with which an organic substance is broken down into simpler molecules in living organisms, releasing energy.

The change in the relative abundances of the isotope of a given element relative to a known abundance either in the past geological record or used as a tracer in biological and chemical process rate measurements.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to 112Cd/110Cd in NIST SRM 3108
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Deviation of the 112Cd/110Cd isotopic ratio of a sample relative to the standard solution SRM 3108, a reference material for cadmium (Cd) developed by the US National Institute of Standards and Technology. It is defined as delta(112/110Cd)NIST =([112Cd/110Cd]sample/[112Cd/110Cd]NIST)-1)×1000. One delta unit represents a one part per 1,000 deviation from the NIST standard composition.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to 114Cd/110Cd in NIST SRM 3108
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Deviation of the 114Cd/110Cd isotopic ratio of a sample relative to the standard solution SRM 3108, a reference material for cadmium (Cd) developed by the US National Institute of Standards and Technology. It is defined as delta(114/110Cd)NIST =([114Cd/110Cd]sample/[114Cd/110Cd]NIST)-1)×1000. One delta unit represents a one part per 1,000 deviation from the NIST standard composition.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to 138Ba/134Ba in NIST SRM 3104a
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Deviation of the 138Ba/134Ba isotopic ratio of a sample relative to the standard solution SRM 3104a, a reference material for Barium (Ba) developed by the US National Institute of Standards and Technology, defined as delta(138/134Ba)NIST =([138Ba/134Ba]sample/[138Ba/134Ba]NIST)-1)×1000. One delta unit represents a one part per 1,000 deviation from the NIST standard composition.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to 143Nd/144Nd in the CHondritic Uniform Reservoir (CHUR)
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Departure of the isotope ratio 143Nd/144Nd from the CHondritic Uniform Reservoir (CHUR) evolution line.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to 56Fe/54Fe in IRMM-14
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Deviation of the isotope ratio 56Fe/54Fe relative to the Institute for Reference Materials and Measurements, Belgium (IRMM) 14 standard.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to 60Ni/58Ni in NIST SRM 986
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Deviation of the 60Ni/58Ni isotopic ratio of a sample relative to the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST, USA) standard solution SRM 986.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to 66Zn/64Zn in IRMM-3702
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Deviation of the isotope ratio zinc-66/zinc-64 relative to the Institute for Reference Materials and Measurements, Belgium (IRMM) 3702 standard. It is defined as delta(66Zn/64Zn)IRMM-3702 =([66Zn/64Zn]sample/[66Zn/64Zn]IRMM-3702)-1)×1000. One delta unit represents a one part per 1,000 deviation from the IRMM-3702 standard composition.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to 66Zn/64Zn in Lyon JMC 3-0749
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Deviation of the isotope ratio zinc-66/zinc-64 relative to the Lyon standard JMC 3-0749, a reference material for zinc developed at the Ecole Normale Supérieure of Lyon using Johnson-Matthey Company (JMC) metal stock 3-0749. It is defined as delta(66Zn/64Zn)Lyon-JMC =([66Zn/64Zn]sample/[66Zn/64Zn]Lyon-JMC)-1)×1000. One delta unit represents a one part per 1,000 deviation from the Lyon-JMC standard composition.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to Lyon JMC 3-0749
skos:Concept.skos:definition: Abundance of an isotope of a given element reported relative to a standard solution developed at the Ecole Normale Supérieure of Lyon using Johnson-Matthey Company (JMC) metal stock 3-0749 and known as the 'Lyon' standard for zinc.
The change in the relative abundance of an isotope of a given element relative to the reference abundance measured in Vienna Standard Mean Ocean Water (VSMOW).

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to Vienna Pee Dee Belemnite (VPDB)
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The change in the relative abundance of an isotope of a given element relative to the reference abundance measured in Vienna Pee Dee Belemnite.

skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: Enrichment with respect to the VSMOW-SLAP scale
skos:Concept.skos:definition: The change in the relative abundance of an isotope of a given element relative to the value given on a scale formed by the reference materials Vienna Standard Mean Ocean Water (VSMOW) and Standard Light Antarctic Precipitation (SLAP).
The rate at which an organism disposes of a substance as solid waste.

Difference between the measured activity of a radioactive isotope and the activity of that isotope predicted from equilibrium in-situ decay of its parent in a decay scheme. This difference is used as the basis for radiometric dating.
Indication of whether or not a specified gene is present in an organism.
The effective partial pressure of a gas allowing for the non-ideal nature of the gas phase.
The difference between the fugacity of a gas in a sample in equilibrium with water minus the fugacity of this gas in an air sample.
The proportion of a substance or biomass removed per unit time through being eaten.
The increase in biomass of an organism per unit time.
The amount of new biomass produced per unit of organic C substrate assimilated.
The quantity of plant pigments in the gut of an organism.
The longest horizontal dimension of an object
The amount of a specified substance in a unit amount of another substance or matrix corrected for variation in lipid content.
The logarithmic value of the stability constant for the formation of a complex formed by the interaction of a metal ion with a ligand in solution.
The amount of a specified substance.
The calculated ratio of the amount of two specified substances.
Ratio of the amount expressed in moles of a component divided by the total number of moles of all constituents in a mixture.
Ratio of the amount expressed in moles of a component divided by the total number of moles of all constituents in an air sample at 100% humidity (sometimes also labelled 'wet air').
Ratio of the amount expressed in moles of a component divided by the total number of moles of all constituents in an air sample after removal of water vapour.
A count of genetically identical organisms

The speed at which a chemical species increases its oxidation number by losing electrons or, in organic chemistry, gaining oxygen or losing hydrogen. Oxidation is coupled with reduction in redox reactions.
The pressure exerted by a gas as part of a gas mixture.
The rate at which a substance or an entity is produced.
A quantified subset of an entity.
A quantified subset of an entity based on dry weight.
A quantified subset of an entity based on counts.
A quantified subset of an entity based on volume.

A quantified subset of an entity based on weight or volume; usage of this code should be restricted to situations when it is not possible to know whether weight or volume was used to derive the proportion.
The quantified subset of eggs hatching.
A part or amount considered in relation to the total fatty acids in a sample or entity. A fatty acid being a carboxylic acid with a long aliphatic tail chain.

The speed at which a chemical species decreases its oxidation number by gaining electrons or, in organic chemistry, losing oxygen or gaining hydrogen. Reduction is coupled to oxidation in redox reactions.
The number of one entity per unit area or per unit volume relative to another.
The proportion of an organism combining with a genetic probe.
Mass or volume of a substance passing from a river into the sea usually stated over a period of time.

A ratio of the measured concentration of a dissolved element or compund in the water to the maximum amount of that element or compound that will dissolve in the water at that temperature and pressure under stable equilibrium.
The quantity of an entity gravitationally settling through a medium per unit area per unit time.
A randomly-oriented measurement of the dimension of an object.
The rate at which a substance or an entity is consumed.
The speed with which a substance is taken in by cellular organisms or organs.
The amount of 3-dimensional space occupied by an object
